schedule.text:
Desiring to make provision
            for the reciprocal surrender of fugitive
            offenders;

(i) murder
            (including attempted murder) or manslaughter, including criminal negligence causing
            death;

(iv) offences
            of a sexual nature including rape; sexual assault; indecent assault; unlawful sexual
            acts on children; child pornography; statutory sexual offences;

(v)
                 gross
            indecency with a child, a mental defective or an unconscious person;

(vi) kidnapping;
            abduction; false imprisonment; unlawful confinement; dealing or trafficking in slaves or
            other persons; taking a hostage;

(xi) offences
            against the law relating to companies including offences committed by officers,
            directors, and promoters;

(xiii) any
            offence relating to counterfeiting; any offence against the law relating to forgery or
            uttering what is forged;

(xv) an
            offence against the law relating to bribery, corruption, secret commissions, and breach
            of trust;

(xxi) an
            offence against laws relating to environmental pollution or protection of public
            health;

(xxvii) an
            offence against the laws relating to the control of exportation or importation of goods
            of any type, or the international transfer of funds;

(xxviii) smuggling;
            offences against the laws relating to import and export of prohibited items, including
            historical and archaeological items and wildlife and endangered species;

(xxxiii) stealing,
            abandoning, neglecting or unlawfully detaining a child: any other offence involving the
            exploitation of children;

(xxxiv) offences
            against the laws relating to prostitution and premises kept for the purposes of
            prostitution;

(xxxvi) revenue
            offences, including offences relating to fiscal matters, taxes or duties and
            customs;

(xl) offences
            relating to the possession or laundering of proceeds obtained from the commission of any
            offence for which surrender may be granted under this Agreement;

(xli) impeding
            the arrest or prosecution of a person who has or is believed to have committed an
            offence for which surrender may be granted under this Agreement;

(b) the
            offence for which surrender is sought was committed within the jurisdiction of its
            courts;

(a) shall,
            if the requesting Party so requests, hand over to the requesting Party all articles,
            including sums of money,

(c) any
            other offence for which surrender may be granted under this Agreement in respect of
            which the requested Party may consent to his or her being dealt with;
